 clearly deprioritized the needs of deaf individuals, and 2) the case highlights why more deaf and otherwise impaired people should be involved in government. %0a%3c %0a%3c Another alarming fact about this case was that the fraudulent interpreter embezzled money from a private school meant for special needs children, including deaf children. Part of the reason she was able to get away with this scheme for many years was the vulnerable position deaf individuals are put into. This is not to say deaf people are weaker than hearing people, but rather that they are more likely to be ignored by the hearing people. Compound that with the fact that deaf people occupy disproportionately low positions of power, and their specific needs can be ignored. After all, deaf people are more likely to actually address the needs of other deaf people.%0a%3c %0a%3c https://themindhears.org/2019/07/16/under-represented-where-are-all-the-deaf-and-hard-of-hearing-academics/%0a%3c %0a%3c https://www.wfla.com/8-on-your-side/unqualified-asl-poser-with-criminal-past-dupes-police-at-seminole-heights-killer-news-conference/%0a%3c %0a%3c https://www.wfla.com/8-on-your-side/investigations/fake-asl-interpreter-at-tampa-police-news-conference-served-prison-time-for-stealing-from-special-needs-kids/%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {